FBIS3-30424 "dreeu023_k_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-023 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Feb 1994 CROATIA Poll Shows Tudjman's Popularity Rising AU0202181094 AU0202181094 Article Type:BFN [Editorial Report] Zagreb GLOBUS in Serbo-Croatian on 28 January on pages 2 and 9 carries an approximately 3,500-word report on the results of GLOBUS' "big" poll on the popularity of Croatian politicians and political parties. The report, entitled "Although More Than 90 Percent of Croats Are Dissatisfied, President Tudjman's Popularity Is Rising," does not contain any information on how the poll was conducted. The only information concerning the size of the sample is that "2,120 citizens were approached" and that "more than 1,100 did not refuse to answer the questions." The results of the poll's question on the popularity of Croatian President Franjo Tudjman and Drazen Budisa, leader of the main opposition party, the Croatian Social Liberal Party (HSLS), are expressed in percentages and show the following: ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |28 Jul 93 |16 Nov 93 |21 Dec 93 |21 Jan 94 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Tudjman |49.9 |46.1 |47 |49.1 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Budisa |29.2 |27.5 |26.8 |20.9 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- Regarding the popularity of the ruling Croatian Democratic Community and the HSLS, the results show the following: ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |28 Jul 93 |16 Nov 93 |21 Dec 93 |21 Jan 94 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |HDZ |29.1 |35.5 |43.8 |36.6 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |HSLS |38.8 |36.9 |31.8 |30.6 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- The respondents' answers to the question "What, in your view, is the mood among the citizens of the Republic of Croatia" reveal the following: ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |They are dissatisfied |54.5 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |They are very dissatisfied |38.9 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |They are satisfied |6 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |They are very satisfied |0.6 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- The respondents' answers to the question "How would you assess your standard of living under the current circumstances in our society" show the following: ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Average |37.5 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Slightly lower than average |22.8 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Considerably lower than average |28.3 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Slightly higher than average |6.5 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Considerably higher than average |1.8 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Do not know |3.1 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- According to the report, out of the 2,120 citizens who were asked the question "Who would you elect as president of the republic," 618 respondents said they did not know, 170 did not want to answer the question, and 326 said they would not take part in the elections. The results of the remaining 1,006 respondents show the following: ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |21 Dec 93 |21 Jan 94 | ----------------------------------